2 §100.257. Criminal Justice Technology Innovation Fund
3 There is hereby established in the state treasury, as a special fund, the
4 Criminal Justice Technology Innovation Fund, hereinafter referred to as the "fund".
5 Any money transferred, donated, or appropriated to the fund by the legislature shall
6 be deposited into the fund after compliance with the requirements of Article VII,
7 Section 9(B) of the Constitution of Louisiana relative to the Bond Security and
8 Redemption Fund. All unexpended and unencumbered monies in the fund at the end
9 of the fiscal year shall remain in the fund. The monies in the fund shall be invested
10 by the state treasurer in the same manner as monies in the state general fund, and
11 interest earned on the investment of monies in the fund shall be credited to the fund.
12 Notwithstanding the provisions of Chapter 17 of Title 39 of the Louisiana Revised
13 Statutes of 1950, monies in the fund shall be used by offices of the district attorney
14 to leverage technology to collaborate with other entities and facilitate interagency
15 communication regarding care and protection of youth.
16 §100.258. Strategic Investments Across Louisiana Fund
17 There is hereby established in the state treasury, as a special fund, the
18 Strategic Investments Across Louisiana Fund, hereinafter referred to as the "fund".
