28 §1533. Self-Insurance Fund
29 A.(1) There is hereby created in the Department of the Treasury a special
30 fund to be known as the "Self-Insurance Fund". The fund shall consist of all
31 premiums paid by state agencies under the state's risk management program as
32 established by this Chapter, the investment income earned from such premiums, and
33 commissions retained in accordance with the provisions of this Title. This fund shall
34 be used only for the payment of losses incurred by state agencies under the
35 self-insurance program, premiums for insurance obtained through commercial
36 carriers, administrative expenses associated with the management of the state's risk,
37 law enforcement officers and firemen's survivors benefits as provided for in R.S.
38 40:1665(C) and 1665.2(C), law enforcement officers and firemen's disability benefits
39 as provided for in R.S. 40:1668, the payment of extraordinary medical and dental
40 expenses for firemen and law enforcement officers as provided for in R.S. 40:1668.1,
41 the payment of losses incurred by the Jefferson Parish Human Services Authority in
42 accordance with R.S. 28:831(J), the payment of losses incurred by the Capital Area
43 Human Services District in accordance with R.S. 28:906, the payment of losses
44 incurred by the Florida Parishes Human Services Authority in accordance with R.S.
45 28:856, the payment of losses incurred by the Metropolitan Human Services District
46 in accordance with R.S. 28:866, the payment of losses incurred by the Northeast
47 Delta Human Services Authority in accordance with R.S. 28:896, the payment of
48 losses incurred by the South Central Louisiana Human Services Authority in
49 accordance with R.S. 28:876, and the funding of the legal services, such funds to be
50 administered by the commissioner of administration.
51 (2) Payments for law enforcement officers and firemen survivor and
52 disability benefits and extraordinary medical and dental expenses as provided for in
53 R.S. 40:1665(C), 1665.2(C), and 1668, and 1668.1 shall be made by the office of risk
54 management on behalf of the Law Enforcement Officers and Firemen's Survivor
55 Benefit Review Board as a result of a specific appropriation received for that
56 purpose. Aggregate payments made pursuant to this Paragraph shall not exceed five
57 million dollars in any given fiscal year.
